    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "Office Memorandum • UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "text": "TO : MR. A. H. BELMONT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "FROM : MR. [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "SUBJECT: FLYING SAUCERS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "DATE: September 27, 1950",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "SAC Cornelius of Philadelphia called at 10:45 A.M.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "today and stated that yesterday evening while two officers of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "the Philadelphia Police Department were cruising in their",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "scout car they saw through the windshield an object descending",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "slowly to the earth which appeared at first glance to be a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "parachute.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "When the officers first noticed the object, it was at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "tree-top level and was described as being six feet in diameter.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "It landed in a field near-by and the officers, upon examining it,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "noted that it gave out a purplish glow which was almost a mist.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "The officers summoned two other police officers. After looking",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "at the object for some time they attempted to pick it up. The",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "object broke, leaving a slight odorless residue. Over a period",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "of about 25 minutes which the officers spent watching the object",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "it completely disintegrated. The officers further commented that",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "the object was so light that when it hit the field, it did not",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "even bend the weeds or the grass it fell on.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "Mr. Cornelius said that he has called the local office",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "of the Air Force but the individual with whom he spoke there said",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "he knew nothing about them and was not aware that his office was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "looking into reports of this type.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "Mr. Cornelius desired to know what further action should",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "be taken by him.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "I told Mr. Cornelius that he was correct in referring",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "this matter to the local office of OSI and that he should direct",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "a letter to the Bureau incorporating all available information",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "concerning the matter and that we here, upon its receipt, in turn",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "would bring it to the attention of OSI Headquarters.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "LLL:mer",
      "status": "image_matched"
